criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. have one (or more) infant(s) currently admitted in the NICU at the RVH;

          2. intended to provide breast milk to their infant(s);

          3. are able to speak English; and

          4. are willing to be audiotaped during the interview.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Include mothers who:

          1. never intended to breastfeed;

          2. have high risk social situations (for example, known maternal mental illness;
             involvement of youth protection; known alcohol and drug abuse; adoption; identified
             congenital anomalies);

          3. gave birth at term; and

          4. have infants with significant birth defects or serious medical conditions in addition
             to prematurity.
